HEADWORD: Snet
<hw>Snet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G.
<ets>schnitt</ets> that which is cut, fr. <ets>schneiden</ets> to cut,
E. <ets>snath</ets>.]</ety> <def>The fat of a deer.</def> <mark>[Obs. or
Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

